&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Product Owner who can own outcomes, not just artifacts -- and who brings a vision for how AI and intelligent automation can fundamentally improve how back-office operations and controls work. This role blends product thinking, deep financial services operations knowledge, and hands-on experience driving AI-enabled transformation: shaping a roadmap, aligning stakeholders, planning intelligently, and driving execution with transparency. You&#39;ll partner closely with Back Office Operations and Global Business Finance, helping modernize workflows and platforms in a way that is practical, controlled, and genuinely improves how the business runs -- with AI as a core enabler. Our team has a track record of delivering ~95% of projects on time and under budget. We do that by treating ambiguity as work: we break complex initiatives into two phases -- Discovery (to distill the real problem, align stakeholders, and establish a confident plan) and Delivery (to&amp;nbsp;execute with clear milestones, risks, and dependencies).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own discovery. Lead structured discovery efforts to clarify problem statements, current-state workflows, constraints, and success metrics -- then translate that into a plan stakeholders can believe in.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set direction. Build and maintain a product roadmap that balances transformation, near-term&amp;nbsp;outcomes, and operational stability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive AI-enabled transformation. Identify opportunities to embed AI, ML, and intelligent automation into operational workflows -- from reconciliation matching and exception triage to controls monitoring and evidence generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with data science and engineering to&amp;nbsp;move beyond manual processes, designing workflows where AI augments human judgment&amp;nbsp;rather than replacing it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run delivery with discipline. Define milestones, manage dependencies, track progress, and surface risks early.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the connective tissue. Coordinate across business users, engineering, architecture, data&amp;nbsp;science, and leadership; communicate status, tradeoffs, and decisions clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring users along. We use agile practices, but not every user group is mature in agile. You&#39;ll build trust through honest conversations, humility, and transparency --

